cs.SD, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper focuses on incorporating audio into embodied navigation, making this sub-category a strong possibility.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses deep reinforcement learning to train navigation policies, which falls under the umbrella of AI.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although the paper is primarily focused on audio, it also involves visual perception and navigation in 3D environments, which could fall under CV.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper involves developing a pipeline for training navigation policies, which could fall under the sub-category of systems and control.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses deep reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning.
